Greek Prime Minister George Papandreou struggled to cling to power Thursday as he worked to put together a new cabinet and persuade a restive country to stand behind a new round of spending cuts and other concessions needed for the release of emergency loans from the International Monetary Fund.
Defections among Papandreou supporters left his governing coalition with a shrinking majority in the Greek Parliament. Talks over a new cabinet continued late Thursday ahead of an expected call for a vote of confidence in his new government this weekend.
