BEIRUT —Syrian troops backed by tanks moved into the town of Jisr al-Shughour late Friday in an effort to regain control over a swath of territory in northern Syria that appeared to have fallen out of government control.
The offensive came on a day that saw tens of thousands of Syrians take to the streets around the country yet again to call for the ouster of President Bashar al-Assad, in a further sign that the government's use of overwhelming force is not only failing to crush a swelling tide of discontent, but perhaps helping to fuel the unrest.
